    • Method Detail

      • getOrderAuditList

        org.w3c.dom.Document getOrderAuditList(YFSEnvironment env,
                                       org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                       java.rmi.RemoteException

        The getOrderAuditList API returns a list of audits for an Order, or its related entities, such as OrderLines and OrderReleases, or both. Use the getOrderAuditDetails API to get details about the audits.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: None

        Events Raised: None

        Audits: None

        Pre-conditions: None

        Post-conditions: None

        Output Template Support:
        Yes. Some of the elements and attributes are not template driven. Refer to output xml for element level details.

        Database Extensibility Support: Yes
        Yes.

        Parameters:
        inXML - Required. Criteria for which a list of audits must be returned.
        For more information, see the associated input xml files.
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains a list of audits. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
